    "Besides RGB and optical flow streams, Temporal Binding Networks (TBN) Kazakos et al. [25] adds audio as an additional modality as well.",
    "SlowFast Feichtenhofer et al. [8] uses two RGB streams with different resolutions and frame rates.IMGAUD2VID Gao et al.",
    "[10] introduces a video skimming mechanism for untrimmed videos, aided by audio, to eliminate both short-term and long-term redundancies.",
    "Accordingly, it uses audio to extract dynamic scene information along with a single frame that captures most of the appearance information, in order to form an image-audio pair.",
    "These pairs are then used to select key moments from the video for action recognition."
